li.al:
"income tested benefit" means any benefit where
                eligibility for or the rate of it is dependent on the income of
                any person;

``social security laws" means in relation to a
                    Contracting Party the laws specified in Article 2 in
                    relation to that Contracting Party;

``New Zealand" means New Zealand only (and not the
                    Cook Islands, Niue and Tokelau); ``The Netherlands"
                    means the Kingdom of the Netherlands in Europe;

``national" means in relation to New Zealand, a New
                    Zealand citizen and in relation to the Netherlands, a person
                    of Netherlands nationality;

in determining the number of whole months residence in New
                  Zealand, only residence after attaining the age of 20 years
                  shall be taken into account;

in relation to a person who reached the age of 65 prior to
                  the date that this Agreement came into force, that person has
                  resided in New Zealand, at any time, for at least 10 years;

in determining the number of whole months residence in New
                  Zealand, only residence in New Zealand since attaining the age
                  of 20 years shall be taken into account;

the maximum amount of benefit payable shall be the maximum
                  rate of benefit which that person would be entitled to receive
                  under the legislation of New Zealand;

the enforcement of the social security debt is permitted
                    in the State of the requesting institution and citing the
                    relevant legislation authorising its enforcement;

a certified copy of the claimant's identification
                    such as passport, birth certificate, marriage certificate or
                    drivers license;

verification of the Netherlands pension reference number
                    and/or social fiscal number of the claimant, his or her
                    spouse and dependent children;

each Liaison Body will produce a report for the other
                    Contracting Party on the Privacy Laws in force in its
                    jurisdiction that may affect the exchange of information;

names and birth dates and place of birth of dependent
                    children including those between 16 and 18 years who are
                    still at school;

income details of the claimant or recipient and their
                    spouse or partner and their dependent children, including
                    income generated from assets;

"inkomensgetoetste uitkering": elke uitkering waarbij het
                inkomen van een persoon bepaalt of hij ervoor in aanmerking komt
                of waarbij het inkomen bepalend is voor de hoogte van de uitkering;

``Nieuw-Zeeland": uitsluitend Nieuw-Zeeland (en niet
                    de Cook eilanden, Niue en Tokelau); ``Nederland": het
                    Koninkrijk der Nederlanden in Europa;

``onderdaan": met betrekking tot Nieuw-Zeeland, een
                    Nieuw-Zeelands staatsburger en, met betrekking tot
                    Nederland, een persoon van de Nederlandse nationaliteit;

voor het vaststellen van het aantal hele maanden van wonen
                  in Nieuw-Zeeland wordt slechts wonen na het bereiken van de
                  leeftijd van 20 jaar in aanmerking genomen;

voor het vaststellen van het aantal hele maanden van wonen
                  in Nieuw-Zeeland wordt slechts wonen na het bereiken van de
                  leeftijd van 20 jaar in aanmerking genomen;

het te betalen maximale uitkeringsbedrag is de maximum
                  uitkering waarop die persoon aanspraak zou hebben ingevolge de
                  Nieuw-Zeelandse wetgeving;
